{
  "id": "S2R17700",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "BROWSE",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "menu",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The BROWSE command opens a nested browse session, thereby allowing you"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "to browse another file without having to terminate your current browse"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "session. When the nested browse session is terminated, the current"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "session resumes."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "You may invoke a nested browse session from within browse by entering the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "BROWSE+line command.  The format of this command is:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "BROWSE <path\\filename>"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "For example:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "COMMAND  browse xyz     + causes browse to be entered recursively"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "and file \"xyz\" in the current directory"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "to be displayed."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "COMMAND  browse         + causes browse to be entered recursively"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "and the BrowseEntry panel to be"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "displayed."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Hit"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+to return to previous menu)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
